# === Session scratch / local-only working dirs (keep on disk, don't track) ===
# Unzipped marketplace pack source (the zip is the SSOT; this is an extract-on-demand working copy).
Tools/_laser_src/
# Skill BUNDLES dropped into Tools/skills as raw .skill ZIPs (the visual-spec source, e.g.
# expert-game-designer.skill). Installed skills live in Tools/skills/<name>/SKILL.md folders; the
# raw bundles are local references, not tracked.
Tools/skills/*.skill
# Temporary diagnostic content (B_*_AssignCharacterPart probes etc) — session scratch, never shipped.
Content/_TmpDiag/
# Agent scratch markers
Tools/_commit_msg*.txt
Tools/_commit_canary.txt
Tools/_gate2_live.png

# === EOS credentials — SECRET-SAFE (Track-2 EOS auth lane) ===
# The real Config/Custom/EOS/DefaultEngine.ini carries the operator's EOS ClientSecret +
# the 5 product IDs. UE's CustomConfig layering merges ONLY this named file (no #include,
# no arbitrary extra .ini), so the secret MUST live in this file — therefore the file is
# gitignored and only DefaultEngine.ini.example (placeholders, secret-free) is committed.
# Operator: copy the .example to DefaultEngine.ini, fill the 6 values, never commit.
Config/Custom/EOS/DefaultEngine.ini
!Config/Custom/EOS/DefaultEngine.ini.example

# === AFL hygiene (2026-06-23): marketplace demo dupes + parked vendor plugin ===
# Marketplace / anim-pack Demo/ subtrees are unreferenced demo dupes. Verified safe: the only
# tracked content that reaches into Demo/ (the FreeAnimationLibrary climb anims -> SK_Mannequin)
# depends solely on already-committed assets; the ignored remainder (SKM_Manny_Simple, demo
# materials/textures/maps) has no inbound refs. gitignore never untracks, so nothing committed is
# affected -- this only keeps the dupes out of `git status`.
**/Demo/
# OmniWalk vendor plugin: PARKED (kept on disk, not committed, not deleted) -- needed later for the
# gravity-gun lane. Untracked + ignored so it stops cluttering status without being lost.
/Plugins/OmniWalk07f218f7e14eV2/

